// Connection Pooling Anti-Patterns — AVOID:
// ❌ Opening a new connection per request
// ❌ Not setting max_connections (default can be too low)
// ❌ No timeout configuration (hangs on network issues)
// ❌ No health checks (stale connections fail mysteriously)
// ❌ Forgetting to close connections in error paths

# Recommended pool sizes:
# - Small app (< 100 req/s): 10-20 connections
# - Medium app (100-1000 req/s): 20-50 connections
# - Large app (> 1000 req/s): 50-200 connections
# Rule of thumb: pool_size = (peak_requests_per_second * avg_response_time_ms) / 1000
